H0.text: state the process that divides one nucleus into two genetically identical nuclei. Cytokinesis

H1.text: state the process that divides one nucleus into two genetically identical nuclei. Endoreduplication

H2.text: state the process that divides one nucleus into two genetically identical nuclei. Meiosis

H3.text: state the process that divides one nucleus into two genetically identical nuclei. mitosis

A4.text: Mitosis is a part of the cell cycle in eukaryotic cells in which replicated chromosomes are separated into two new nuclei.

A5.text: Instead of being divided into two new daughter nuclei, the replicated chromosomes are retained within the original nucleus. The cells then re-enter G1 and S phase and replicate their chromosomes again.
